---
description: Run security and test coverage checks before every git commit
alwaysApply: true
---

Before staging or running `git commit`, run `npm run precommit` and fix all errors.

- `npm run precommit` runs security checks and tests with **80% minimum coverage** on `src/lib/**`.
- Never commit `.env` or `.env.local` files.
- Never bypass the pre-commit hook with `--no-verify` unless the user explicitly asks.
- When adding or changing code in `src/lib/**`, add or update unit/integration tests to keep coverage above 80%.
- For changes to auth, middleware, API routes, admin actions, or `next.config.ts`, mention that a manual security review is recommended before pushing.
